# Student Grade Management System

A simple full-stack web application for managing student grades.

Built using:
- Python (Flask backend)
- HTML/CSS/JavaScript (frontend)
- Text file storage (grades.txt)

---

## Features

- Add student name and grades
- Automatically calculate average
- Assign letter grade (A–F)
- Store results in file
- View saved records
- Simple and extendable architecture

---

## Project Structure

StudentGradeSystem/
│
├── app.py              # Flask backend server
├── grades.txt          # Data storage
├── requirements.txt    # Dependencies
│
├── templates/          # Dynamic HTML pages
│   └── index.html
│
├── static/             # Static assets
│   ├── css/
│   ├── js/
│
└── README.md

---

## Installation

1. Clone project
2. Install dependencies

pip install flask

---

## Run the app

python app.py

Open browser:
http://127.0.0.1:5000

---

## How it Works

Frontend → Flask → File Storage

1. User submits grades via form
2. Flask processes data
3. Calculates average and letter grade
4. Saves to grades.txt
5. Displays result

---

